        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 4:46AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 444 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms over
Throckmorton County, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elbert, Lusk, Woodson, Throckmorton, and rural areas of Throckmorton
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
